segment tree can=E2=80=99t handle. We will learn how to take numbers on a s=
egment modulo some number, apply the min=3D and max=3D operations, add +=3D=
 to them, and also find GCD on a segment with these operations. And all the=
 proofs are gonna be super simple, so don=E2=80=99t be scared, it will be e=
asy! In the next video, we will cover even more awesome queries, so stay tu=
ned.</p><p><a href=3D"https://youtu.be/NwkO73jGSPA">Link to the video</a></=
p><p>You can check out my previous videos on <a href=3D"https://www.youtube=
.com/c/peltorator">my channel</a></p><p>Contest on Segment Tree Beats (and =
others) is <a href=3D"https://codeforces.com/group/1rv4rhCsHp/contests">her=
e</a></p><p>Also, there's the Russian version of this video if you speak Ru=
ssian <a href=3D"https://youtu.be/58csqxAD8vM">here</a></p><p><img alt=3D" =
" src=3D"https://codeforces.com/predownloaded/47/25/47253e8a4d9533f695452d8=
c4b52b0332ca5e4bb.png" style=3D"max-width: 100.0%;max-height: 100.0%;"></p>=
<p><a href=3D"https://codeforces.com/blog/entry/57319">Original article in =
English</a></p><p><a href=3D"http://www.doc88.com/p-6744902151779.html">Ori=
ginal article in Chinese</a></p><p>Implementations of algorithms from this =
video:</p><p><a href=3D"https://pastebin.com/wabDfjKi">%=3D on a segment, =
=3D in a point, sum on a segment</a></p><p><a href=3D"https://pastebin.com/=
bEEQsDr7">Ji Driver Segment Tree (min=3D on a segment, sum on a segment)</a=
></p><p><a href=3D"https://pastebin.com/UJhuFA3a">min=3D on a segment, max=
